<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Chargé in Saudi Arabia (
                        Sands
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d458</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">458</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-06T00:54:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-06T00:54:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-06T00:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-06T00:54:00-05:00" n="458" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/5–646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sands</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-06T09:00:00+03:06">May 6, 1946—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>129. (1) Sheikh Iusuf Yassin Deputy <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>
                    returned yesterday afternoon from Riyadh and departed early this morning for
                    Cairo where he will discuss Palestine inquiry report with Arab League officials
                    (Legtel 127, May 5<note n="29" xml:id="d458fn29">Not printed.</note>). He told
                    me on arrival only that the reaction of the King to the report was “very
                    bad”.</p>
                <p>(2) I am informed that staff members of British Legation here in conversation
                    with Saudis are successfully conveying impression that recommendation for entry
                    of hundred thousand Jews into Palestine was one purely of American origin
                    against which British members struggled unsuccessfully.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sands</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
